You.
I Think We Should
Lose The Account.

00:28.000 --> 00:30.700
What?
We Don't Need Atlantic Attire
Or Their Money.

00:30.700 --> 00:34.700
So You Want
To Destroy "Mode"?
Well, There's Only Room

00:35.000 --> 00:36.700
At Meade Publications.

00:36.800 --> 00:39.300
So The Baby's Yours.
I'm Soy, Betty.

00:39.300 --> 00:40.600
You Should Go.

00:43.100 --> 00:45.800
Henry, I'm Sorry.
I Just Can't See You.

00:45.800 --> 00:47.400
Not With The Way
Everything Turned Out.

00:47.400 --> 00:48.600
The Baby's Yours.

00:48.600 --> 00:50.600
You're Going Back To Tucson
To Be With Charlie.

00:50.600 --> 00:53.000
I Am Not Going Back
To Be With Charlie.

00:53.100 --> 00:55.500
I Am Going Back
To Be A Father To My Child.

00:55.500 --> 00:57.500
Maybe We Can
Still Do This.

00:57.500 --> 01:00.300
Long Distance? It--
That'll Never Work.

01:00.300 --> 01:02.900
I Just Think It's Better
If We Just Avoid Each Other

01:03.000 --> 01:04.400
Until You Leave.

01:04.500 --> 01:07.100
So That's It.
Just Like That?

01:07.100 --> 01:09.300
Yes, I Think
That's What's Best.

01:09.300 --> 01:12.600
Excuse Me, Do You Mind
Not Leaning On Me?
Who's Leaning On You?

01:12.600 --> 01:14.400
Well, You See,
That's None Of Your Concern.

01:14.400 --> 01:16.100
People Can Lean On Me
All They Want.
Okay.

01:16.100 --> 01:19.800
No, Not You.
Okay, So I'm Here
For Five More Months.

01:19.800 --> 01:23.500
How Do We Make This Work?
When You Need
Daniel's Signature, Send Kenny.

01:23.500 --> 01:25.500
Okay. What About Meals?

01:25.600 --> 01:28.800
I Go To The Cafeteria
At 1:00.
I Guess I Can Do 12:00.

01:28.900 --> 01:31.300
Except For Taco Tuesdays.
I'm Always Afraid

01:31.400 --> 01:34.600
They're Gonna Run Out,
So I Have To Go Early.
Okay, Sure.

01:35.600 --> 01:37.900
Well, Maybe This Whole
Avoidance Thing Will Work.

01:37.900 --> 01:41.000
Yeah, We Never Have To
See Each Other At All.

01:45.700 --> 01:46.100
Ugh!

