01:50.300 --> 01:53.000
Starting Tomorrow,
I'll Take The Subway.

01:53.800 --> 01:55.000
Uh-Huh.

01:59.300 --> 01:59.600
Morning.

01:59.800 --> 02:02.600
Hey, Don't Fill Up On Fruit.
I'm Making <I>Machaca.</I>

02:02.700 --> 02:05.200
Oh, No, I Can't Stay.
It's Thursday.

02:05.200 --> 02:06.900
Santos And I Do
Our Lotto Scratchers

02:06.900 --> 02:08.699
At The Cemetery.
Oh.

02:10.300 --> 02:12.200
Hey, Kiddo.
I'm Making <I>Machaca.</I>

02:12.300 --> 02:14.900
I Know You Say
It Gives You Hips But--
I'm Meeting My Friends.

02:14.900 --> 02:17.400
Oh, Are You All Trying Out
For "The Music Man"?

02:17.400 --> 02:19.700
I Read In The School Paper
Auditions Are Today.

02:19.800 --> 02:22.300
Drama Club?
That's For Losers.

02:22.300 --> 02:24.800
You're The President.
You Even Started The Club.

02:25.300 --> 02:26.500
Whatever. Here.

02:27.100 --> 02:28.200
Oh.

02:29.900 --> 02:31.400
Okay. Bye.

02:32.500 --> 02:33.600
Hey.

02:33.600 --> 02:37.000
Do You Even Know
What You Signed?
Oh, I Don't Know, <I>Papi.</I>

02:37.600 --> 02:40.000
Maybe It Was
For Mail-Order Crack.

02:40.000 --> 02:43.000
Come On, It Was
A Permission Slip For Something.

02:43.000 --> 02:45.500
It's Fine. Bye.

02:48.800 --> 02:50.900
Did You Get It?

02:50.900 --> 02:53.000
One Note Excusing Me
From The Field Trip Tomorrow.

02:53.000 --> 02:55.500
Yeah, Suck That,
Queens County Farm Museum.

02:55.700 --> 02:57.700
So What
Are We Gonna Do?

02:57.700 --> 02:59.600
We'll Take My Family's Car
Out For A Ride.

02:59.600 --> 03:01.100
My Dad Taught Me
How To Drive.

03:01.400 --> 03:03.000
Car Thieves Are Hot.

03:05.200 --> 03:08.100
Marc Jacobs Wants To Send
Over Bags. I Said Yes.

03:08.100 --> 03:11.000
Kathy Griffin Is Begging
For A Date. I Said No.

03:11.000 --> 03:13.400
And Your Father Wants To Have
You And Alexis Over For Dinner

03:13.400 --> 03:15.900
With Him And Wilhelmina.
I Didn't Know What To Say.

03:15.900 --> 03:19.100
Great. I Get To Spend Time
With My Futurestep-Monster.

03:19.100 --> 03:22.700
One Big Crappy Family.
A Grudging "Yes" It Is.
Speaking Of Which,

03:22.700 --> 03:24.700
Your Step-Monster Has Called
A Meeting In Her Office

03:24.700 --> 03:27.100
In 30 Seconds.
Wait, Is That Why
We're Headed This Way?

03:27.100 --> 03:28.800
I Was Hoping We Were
Going To Get Danish.

03:31.500 --> 03:32.600
Are You Really
That Good,

03:32.600 --> 03:34.100
Or Did You Just Happen
To Have That On You?

03:34.100 --> 03:36.200
You'll Never Know. Oh.

03:38.700 --> 03:40.000
Are You Okay With This?

03:40.000 --> 03:41.500
You Can Skip The Meeting
If You Want.

03:41.500 --> 03:44.500
No, I Won't Let This
Get In The Way Of My Job.

03:44.700 --> 03:45.700
I'm A Professional.

03:45.700 --> 03:47.900
Besides, It's Not Like
I'm Writing "Betty Loves Henry"

03:47.900 --> 03:49.300
All Over My Notebook.

03:49.300 --> 03:50.600
Um, You--
Shut Up.

03:54.100 --> 03:55.900
(Wilhelmina) Thank You
For Joining Us, Daniel.

03:55.900 --> 03:57.900
Why Are You In Here? Where Are
All The Other Departments?

03:58.000 --> 04:00.400
Oh, I Only Invited Ad Sales
And Accounting.

04:00.400 --> 04:01.300
I Figured It'd Be Easier

04:01.400 --> 04:04.300
To Discuss
The Advertising Situation

04:04.300 --> 04:07.600
In A Smaller,
Le Judgmental Group.
(Whispering) Excuse Me,

04:07.800 --> 04:10.900
Over There To That Chair?
Well, That's Very Thoughtful
Of You, Wilhelmina,

04:11.000 --> 04:15.000
But I Really Don't Have
Anything To Hide.

04:15.500 --> 04:16.100
I've Been Very Open
About This Whole Thing.

04:16.200 --> 04:18.800
And If You Could Just Move
To That Chair. It's Empty.

04:18.800 --> 04:20.000
I Think We All Know
Atlantic Attire

04:20.100 --> 04:22.000
Pulled Their Advertising
From "Mode."
(Normal Voice) No, No, No.

04:22.000 --> 04:25.700
I Didn't Mean You.
I Meant Him.
Betty? Please.

04:25.700 --> 04:28.100
Oh, You--You Didn't Know?

04:28.100 --> 04:29.800
Uh, Once The News Leaked

04:29.800 --> 04:32.000
That Atlantic Attire
Was Pulling Out,

04:32.000 --> 04:34.400
Well,
Other Companies Followed.

04:34.600 --> 04:37.000
Just How Many Advertisers
Are We Talking About?

04:37.000 --> 04:38.700
Well,
As Of This Morning,

04:38.700 --> 04:41.400
Um... 52%.

04:43.900 --> 04:45.200
(Low Voice) Your Foot
Just Touched My Knee.

04:45.200 --> 04:48.300
(Low Voice) Your Knee
Just Touched My Foot.
Well, Here's The Line.

04:49.400 --> 04:51.200
So What's
Our Financial Outlook?

04:52.000 --> 04:54.800
Well, Uh,
If We Keep Touching--

04:54.800 --> 04:56.500
Spending
At The Current Rate,

04:56.500 --> 04:59.600
Then "Mode" Will Be
Out Of Business In 90 Days.

