05:09.800 --> 05:11.200
(Yoga) Yo, Fish!

05:13.400 --> 05:16.600
You Staying In Here All Day
Or We Gon' Play Tennis?

05:17.000 --> 05:19.900
Yoga,
I've Been Drinking--

05:19.900 --> 05:21.300
I Mean, Thinking.

05:21.300 --> 05:23.600
Uh, Actually,
They're Both Right.

05:23.600 --> 05:26.700
Maybe The South Of France
Isn't Such A Good Idea.

05:26.700 --> 05:28.600
I Am So Glad
To Hear You Say That.

05:28.600 --> 05:31.100
'Cause At Piano Man's
Wine Tasting Last Night,

05:31.100 --> 05:34.700
Everybody Was Saying That
Positano Is The New Monaco.

05:34.700 --> 05:36.700
I Don't Want
To Run Anymore.

05:36.700 --> 05:38.500
I'm Turning Myself In.

05:38.500 --> 05:39.900
Whoa, Whoa,
Whoa, Whoa, Whoa.

05:39.900 --> 05:41.700
That Ain't What
We've Been Talkin' About.

05:41.700 --> 05:43.200
I Can't Leave My Children.

05:43.200 --> 05:44.300
Bradford May Have Moved On,

05:44.300 --> 05:46.700
But Daniel And Alexis
Still Need Me.

05:46.700 --> 05:48.800
Need You?
You Gon' Be In Prison.

05:54.800 --> 05:55.900
I need You.

05:58.100 --> 05:59.700
Between The Two Of Us,
You The One More Likely

05:59.800 --> 06:01.900
To Have A Rich Friend
With An Empty Villa.

06:02.800 --> 06:04.600
Well, At Least If
I'm Behind Bars,

06:04.700 --> 06:05.800
They Can Come Visit.

06:07.700 --> 06:08.900
I'm Sorry, Yoga.

06:10.500 --> 06:12.100
All Right.

06:12.100 --> 06:13.700
If That's The Way
You Want To Play This,

06:13.700 --> 06:15.500
I'm-A Start Packing.

06:15.500 --> 06:17.400
We Don't Have
Anything To Pack.

06:17.400 --> 06:19.900
No, But They Do.

06:22.600 --> 06:24.900
It Was Just Stupid To Think
That We Could Avoid Each Other

06:24.900 --> 06:26.600
When We Work
In The Same Building.

06:26.900 --> 06:27.900
Now I Don't Know
What To Do.

06:28.000 --> 06:30.600
You See, The Problem Is You've
Got No One Else To Focus On.

06:31.300 --> 06:34.800
Not Bad, Not Bad.
Turn. Thank You.

06:36.100 --> 06:37.100
You Need To Date.

06:37.400 --> 06:40.200
Da? No, I Am Not Ready
To Get Involved Again.

06:40.300 --> 06:41.500
Who Said Anything
About Getting Involved?

06:41.600 --> 06:44.800
All You Wanna Do
Is Have A Little Bit Of Fun.
Christina,

06:44.800 --> 06:46.700
Ten Minutes
Before The Fun Happens.

06:46.700 --> 06:48.600
Well, You Don't Know
What You're Missing, Do You?

06:48.600 --> 06:50.200
Okay, Turn.

06:55.200 --> 06:57.200
(Low Voice) Christina, What--
What Are You Doing?

06:57.200 --> 06:58.600
You Can't Alter Underwear.

06:58.600 --> 07:00.100
(Low Voice) Oh,
They Never Catch On.

07:00.800 --> 07:03.300
(Normal Voice)
Okay, Executive Decision--

07:03.300 --> 07:06.900
I'm Gonna Put Your Profile
On Bachelocity.Com.

07:06.900 --> 07:09.800
(Normal Voice) Internet Dating?
There Are Freaks Online.

07:09.800 --> 07:11.400
Why Don't You Just
Chop Me Into Pieces Yourself,

07:11.400 --> 07:14.700
And We Can Cut Out
The Middleman?
Mm, They Don't Always

07:14.700 --> 07:18.500
I Don't Need Internet Dating.
I Can Get Over Henry Myself.

07:18.500 --> 07:19.900
I'm Not <I>That</I> Desperate.

07:19.900 --> 07:21.400
(Man) You're
A Little Desperate.

07:30.800 --> 07:32.300
The Internet It Is.

