07:44.700 --> 07:46.600
"Five Things
I Can't Live Without."

07:46.600 --> 07:50.600
Well, Doughnuts
And My Family...

07:50.800 --> 07:52.200
Ugh, And Eyeglass Cleaner.

07:52.300 --> 07:53.600
I Can't Stand It
When They Get Smudged.

07:53.700 --> 07:56.100
Yeah, You Might Want To
Sex It Up Just A Little Bit.

07:56.100 --> 07:59.400
Why? What Did You Put?
Well, Sex--Five Times.

08:00.100 --> 08:03.000
Oh, Well, Maybe
I'll Come Back To This One.

08:03.300 --> 08:05.600
Oh, Listen, Nobody Cares
About What You Write Anyway.

08:05.600 --> 08:06.700
All They Care About
Is That You've Got

08:06.700 --> 08:09.200
A Cute Little Photograph.
Now Smile.

08:11.400 --> 08:12.000
Ooh.

08:13.800 --> 08:15.700
Oh, No, I Wasn't Ready.
Do Another One.

08:15.700 --> 08:17.500
Okay, Smile.

08:18.000 --> 08:19.300
(Camera Shutter Clicks)
Oh, Well, That One's
A Little Bit Better.

08:19.300 --> 08:22.500
At Least You've Got
One Eye Open.
Head Down, Shoot From Above,

08:22.600 --> 08:24.400
Get Those Bangs To
Cover Those Caterpillars

08:24.400 --> 08:26.600
And Hide Your Chins
By Doing This.

08:27.700 --> 08:29.600
For God Sake,
Lose The Glasses.

08:29.600 --> 08:32.200
Amanda, I Wear Glasses.
I'm Not Gonna Lie.

08:32.299 --> 08:33.299
Whatever.

08:33.400 --> 08:36.100
But Guys Don't Make Passes
At Girls Who Are Fat.

08:36.700 --> 08:38.100
These Are The Shoes
I Borrowed.

08:40.000 --> 08:43.299
You Borrowed The Jimmy Choos.
This Is A Sandwich.

08:43.500 --> 08:45.500
You Usually Don't Open Up
The Box That Fast.

08:46.900 --> 08:47.900
I'll Be Right Back.

08:50.600 --> 08:52.100
Okay,
Let's Try This Again.

08:52.300 --> 08:53.800
Aah, Ham!

08:53.900 --> 08:55.900
Yeah!
That's Your Best One Yet.

08:56.500 --> 08:59.600
Graphics Wants You
To Sign Off On This.
Brilliant.

08:59.900 --> 09:00.900
But You Didn't Even
Look At It.

09:01.000 --> 09:04.100
The First Rule In Ruining
A Magazine Is Stop Caring.

09:04.200 --> 09:05.500
Uh, Why Don't You
Go Downstairs

09:05.600 --> 09:08.900
And Supervise
The Valentino Shoot?
Me? Supervise A Shoot?

09:09.000 --> 09:11.300
Whoa! You've Never Asked Me
To Supervise Anything Before.

09:11.400 --> 09:13.100
Wait A Minute,
Is This Part Of Your Plan

09:13.200 --> 09:16.200
To Make The Magazine Suck?
Do You Care? There'll Be
Male Models In Underwear.

09:16.300 --> 09:18.300
Mm, Not If
I Have My Way.

09:27.400 --> 09:28.500
Knock, Knock.

09:29.900 --> 09:31.500
Your Late.
Take Off Your Clothes.

09:31.500 --> 09:34.500
Ha Ha, Easy Sailor.
Buy A Girl A Drink First.

09:34.600 --> 09:37.400
Oh, I-I'm Sorry, I Thought
You Were The Underwear Model.

09:37.400 --> 09:39.300
Oh, No, No, No, No, No.

09:39.300 --> 09:41.400
I Am Supervising
This Shoot.
(Sizzles)

09:43.200 --> 09:44.400
But It's Funny
That You Mention That

09:44.500 --> 09:46.500
Because I Did Take
A Modeling Class Once.

09:46.500 --> 09:48.700
You Know, Thought About It,
Put It Away,

09:48.700 --> 09:50.800
Could Always Go Back
And Get It.

09:50.900 --> 09:54.400
Hmm, Hmm, Hmm, Hmm.
Ow.

09:56.000 --> 09:57.200
What Are You Laughing At?

09:57.200 --> 09:59.700
You, Uh, You Slapped
Your Own Ass Too Hard.

09:59.700 --> 10:00.600
That's Funny.

10:00.600 --> 10:02.800
Oh, Yeah, I Guess
That Is Funny. Ha Ha.

10:02.800 --> 10:04.600
Cliff St. Paul.
Marc St. James.

10:04.600 --> 10:06.800
Wow, We're Both Saints.
Is Yours Fake, Too?

10:06.900 --> 10:08.000
No.
Mine, Either.

10:08.100 --> 10:11.100
Are You Sure This
Doesn't Make Me Look Fat?

10:12.100 --> 10:13.400
(Sighs) I'll Sign
For That Package.

10:13.400 --> 10:15.800
Well, Please Let Him Be Dumb.
He Can't Have Everything.

10:16.000 --> 10:18.500
Oh. (Laughs)
I Put 'Em On Backward.

10:19.400 --> 10:20.100
Thank You.

10:20.500 --> 10:21.600
I Can Help You.

10:36.600 --> 10:37.200
Hello?

10:37.900 --> 10:39.100
(All) Hello.

10:39.100 --> 10:40.500
Oh, Hey, <I>Papi.</I>

10:40.500 --> 10:42.700
These Are My New Friends
From The Cemetery--

10:42.700 --> 10:46.700
Mabel, Esther, And Lucille.
They Lost Their Husbands, Too.

10:47.200 --> 10:48.400
Heart Attack.

10:48.500 --> 10:49.800
Liver Failure.

10:49.800 --> 10:51.600
Stroke On A Cruise.

10:52.500 --> 10:53.000
I'm Sorry.

10:53.100 --> 10:54.300
You Don't Get
Your Money Back,

10:54.400 --> 10:56.000
But They Don't
Tell You That.

10:56.000 --> 10:59.500
Oh, We're Maki A Quilt
From Our Husbands' Shirts.

10:59.500 --> 11:03.300
Our Dead Husbands.
Fun.

11:08.200 --> 11:10.600
Okay, I Decided
 Go With This One.

11:10.600 --> 11:12.400
I Was Gonna Use The One
That Says,

11:12.400 --> 11:16.400
"Drink Till She's Cute,"
But I Buried Him In It.

11:17.100 --> 11:18.400
(All) Aw.

11:20.100 --> 11:22.100
(Cliff) I Think
The Last Shot's The One.

11:22.100 --> 11:25.000
So This Whole Window Thing
You're Doing, It's Genius.

11:25.000 --> 11:26.900
I Love It.
Totally Get The Concept.

11:26.900 --> 11:30.400
You Have No Idea, Do You?
None Whatsoever.

11:30.400 --> 11:31.900
(Laughs)
Uh, "Rear Window."

11:32.800 --> 11:34.400
Hitchcock?
Never Saw It.

11:34.400 --> 11:36.300
Really?
It--It's Amazing.

11:36.300 --> 11:38.700
I-I-I Love Hitchcock.
What Aut "Psycho"?

11:38.700 --> 11:40.400
Uh, Work For One.
Does That Count?

11:40.400 --> 11:43.100
Hey, Did You Guys
See "Saw"?

11:43.100 --> 11:44.300
No.

11:44.300 --> 11:46.100
Wh--I Said "Seesaw."
(Laughs)

11:49.300 --> 11:49.800
Wow.

11:50.100 --> 11:51.800
(Gasps) I Know. Oh.

11:51.800 --> 11:54.100
Okay, You Have To Go
With Me Tomorrow Night.

11:54.100 --> 11:57.300
I'm Seeing "Psycho"
At The Film Forum.
Oh, That Sounds Like Fun.

11:57.300 --> 11:59.200
Maybe We Could
Grab A Beer Before.

11:59.200 --> 12:01.900
Uh, Sure, If By "Beer"
You Mean "Appletini."

12:01.900 --> 12:02.900
Okay.

12:03.900 --> 12:05.700
Gus, Rear Back
In The Window.

12:14.800 --> 12:16.600
What Is It, Girl?
Someone Felldown Their Well?

12:16.600 --> 12:18.700
Betty...
Internet Dating...

12:18.700 --> 12:20.100
Must Mock.

12:20.100 --> 12:21.800
(Gasps) Ooh, Bookmark It.
I Gotta Stick Around Here.

12:21.900 --> 12:22.800
I'm Trying To Work Up
The Nerve

12:22.900 --> 12:24.900
To Ask Out
"Hot Pants" Over There.

12:25.000 --> 12:28.600
Oh, You're Asking <I>Him</I> Out? Maybe
I'll Stay Here And Mock You.

12:28.700 --> 12:30.300
What? You Think
He's Out Of My League?

12:30.400 --> 12:32.300
He's A Nine. I'm An Eight.
He's A Ten. You're A Six.

12:32.400 --> 12:33.800
You're A Bitch.
I'm A Seven.

12:36.200 --> 12:38.400
Now I Know This Is
Going To Hurt A Bit,

12:38.600 --> 12:42.700
But For Starters, We Can
Save 8% By Printing On...

12:43.400 --> 12:44.400
Rice Paper.

12:45.800 --> 12:48.100
Look At That.
That's Not Terrible, Huh?

12:48.100 --> 12:50.700
I Can See You.
(Wilhelmina) Well, We Can
Just Say We're Going Green.

12:50.800 --> 12:53.300
People Will Do Anything If They
Think They're Saving A Tree.

12:53.300 --> 12:57.100
Which Brings Me To...
Soy Ink.

12:57.200 --> 12:59.300
I've Heard That Stuff
Tends To Rub Off.

12:59.400 --> 13:00.800
We Could Throw In
A Packet Of Wasabi,

13:00.900 --> 13:03.400
And Then
We All Got Lunch.
This Is Crazy.

13:03.500 --> 13:06.100
We're Ruining The Magazine,
And It's All My Fault.

13:06.100 --> 13:08.100
No, It's Not. It's My Fault.

13:08.200 --> 13:10.400
Alexis, I'm The One
Who Lost The Advertisers.

13:10.500 --> 13:12.900
Now, Now,
Stop Blaming Yourselves.

13:13.300 --> 13:14.800
