29:37.950 --> 29:40.500
It's A Perfect Time To Take Our Holiday Photo.

29:40.670 --> 29:43.500
Actually,We Usually Do It In Front Of The Christmas Tree

29:43.670 --> 29:44.800
With Our Real Mother. Come On.

29:44.980 --> 29:45.970
Daniel,I Would Never Try

29:46.140 --> 29:47.840
To Take The Place Of Your Real Mother.

29:48.000 --> 29:49.800
You'll Have Two Christmases This Year--One Here

29:49.980 --> 29:53.600
And One On The Lam. Here,Let Me Take That For You.

29:53.770 --> 29:56.600
Unless You Want To Continue In Your Mother's Tradition.

30:01.540 --> 30:02.990
Thanks,Dad.

30:03.170 --> 30:06.040
All Right, Everyone Smile.

30:14.390 --> 30:16.730
(Yoga Whispering) Hey,Fish.

30:17.310 --> 30:19.480
What The Hell Do You Think You're Doing?

30:19.630 --> 30:22.530
I Don't... I-I Don't Know.

30:23.170 --> 30:26.250
I-I Saw The Gun And... And The Wedding Invitation,

30:26.420 --> 30:29.130
And I Just Lost It.

30:30.660 --> 30:32.390
But Look.

30:33.150 --> 30:36.900
The Woman That Ruined My Life Did What I Never Could.

30:37.090 --> 30:39.070
She Brought Them Together.

30:39.230 --> 30:41.000
They're A Family.

30:43.010 --> 30:45.020
That's All I Ever Wanted.

30:46.540 --> 30:48.330
It's Okay Now.

30:50.410 --> 30:52.370
Let's Go To Italy.

31:02.110 --> 31:04.790
(Hilda) I Gotta Say, This Is Very Relaxing.

31:05.120 --> 31:07.950
It Really Does Pass The Time.

31:08.120 --> 31:09.120
You Know What Else Was Nice?

31:09.290 --> 31:10.350
The Applesauce That We Had For Dinner.

31:10.520 --> 31:12.810
I Think I Could Have It Every Day. (Laughs)

31:12.980 --> 31:16.080
They're Sleeping, Grandma.

31:17.050 --> 31:19.150
For Her,It Could Be The Big One.

31:19.330 --> 31:20.890
<I>Ay,Papi.</I>

31:32.510 --> 31:34.320
It's Not Much, But It's There. (Siren Whoops)

31:35.300 --> 31:38.110
Who Died? I Get Her Clothes.

31:38.260 --> 31:40.450
I'll Get It.

31:46.130 --> 31:47.110
Justin.

31:47.270 --> 31:49.660
Hey,Hilda. Listen,Justin Took Your Car

31:49.840 --> 31:51.990
For A Little Joyride With His Friends.

31:52.150 --> 31:53.640
What?

31:53.810 --> 31:55.600
I'm Goin' Upstairs.

31:55.810 --> 31:58.050
Hey. He Crashed It Into A Tree.

31:58.590 --> 31:59.470
No One Was Hurt

31:59.660 --> 32:02.760
Except The Car And The Tree.

32:03.060 --> 32:04.870
Listen,This One's Between Us.

32:05.040 --> 32:06.160
I Know You Been Goin' Through A Lot Lately,

32:06.320 --> 32:07.600
But Keep An Eye On Him.

32:07.760 --> 32:09.610
I Seen These Things Spiral.

32:09.790 --> 32:12.650
Yeah,Yeah. Thanks,Rita.

32:12.810 --> 32:14.040
Mm-Hmm.

32:14.510 --> 32:16.360
Thanks.

32:23.500 --> 32:24.210
All Right,Ladies.

32:24.370 --> 32:26.350
Looks Like We're Gonna Have To Wrap Things Up.

32:26.500 --> 32:28.860
You Don't Have To Go Home, But You Can't Quilt Here.

32:29.030 --> 32:31.130
Will We See You Tomorrow?

32:31.310 --> 32:34.830
I Don't Think So. I Mean,This Was Fun,

32:34.990 --> 32:36.880
But Maybe I'll Just See You At The Cemetery.

32:37.050 --> 32:38.460
I Mean,Above Ground. (Women Laugh)

32:39.710 --> 32:42.310
So Who's Got The Walker? Yeah,Let's Help.

32:42.780 --> 32:45.520
Well,Dinner Is Served.

32:45.850 --> 32:46.630
Come On.

32:46.800 --> 32:48.640
Soup's Not Soup Unless It's Hot.

32:49.350 --> 32:51.900
Wait,Dad,There's Something I Have To Tell You.

32:52.070 --> 32:52.950
It's About The Magazine.

32:53.120 --> 32:55.610
No,Alexis. I Can't Let You Do That.

32:55.780 --> 32:58.950
Hot Or Cold, Soup Is Soup.

33:03.300 --> 33:05.590
I Lost Atlantic Attire,

33:05.760 --> 33:08.860
Which Led To A Substantial Advertiser Pullout.

33:09.010 --> 33:10.420
How Substantial?

33:10.580 --> 33:11.970
52%, But I Can Explain.

33:12.150 --> 33:14.800
Of All The Incompetent-- Hold On,Dad. It's Not His Fault.

33:14.950 --> 33:17.460
He Was Protecting Me. Don't Defend Him.

33:17.640 --> 33:20.670
Your Brother Has A Long History Of Making Mistakes Around Here

33:20.840 --> 33:23.440
And Expecting Everybody Else To Clean Up After Him.

33:23.610 --> 33:26.000
You're The Only One I Can Count On To Do Anything Right.

33:26.160 --> 33:27.540
And Me,Of Course.

33:27.710 --> 33:30.520
Look,I Can Fix This. Just Give Me The Chance.

33:30.820 --> 33:31.220
(Bradford,Voice Distorted) I Always Knew

33:31.390 --> 33:33.310
Something Like This Wagonna Happen.

33:33.480 --> 33:36.550
You've Had Every Opportunity Handed To You.

33:36.720 --> 33:39.860
How The Hell Could You Turn Into Such A Screwup?

33:40.920 --> 33:43.750
<I>You Are Dead To Me,Alex.</I>

33:46.410 --> 33:48.850
Excuse Me.

33:57.360 --> 34:00.490
Oh,Boy,It Really Is Date Night.

34:01.540 --> 34:02.880
Who Cares?

34:03.030 --> 34:04.340
Two Friends Can Have Dinner,Right?

34:04.510 --> 34:05.360
No Big Deal.

34:05.520 --> 34:06.680
Yeah.

34:08.530 --> 34:09.870
What Are You Doing?

34:10.170 --> 34:12.620
Oh,Oh, This Is For Me.

34:12.780 --> 34:14.639
Sucks To Be You.

34:14.810 --> 34:16.480
No,Seriously, Do You Want To Sit Here?

34:16.650 --> 34:19.040
No,I'm Fine.

34:20.639 --> 34:21.780
Thank You.

34:22.420 --> 34:23.800
Thank You.

34:24.600 --> 34:27.110
Oh,Look, It's My Date's Bird.

34:27.280 --> 34:29.260
Guess He Didn't Make It.

34:29.480 --> 34:31.610
I'm Sorry. I'm A Terrible Liar.

34:31.770 --> 34:33.520
????

34:33.690 --> 34:35.710
And You're On A Bowling Team Called The Debitz?

34:35.870 --> 34:39.610
No,The Debitz Are Real. It Just Wasn't League Night. Oh.

34:40.540 --> 34:44.010
I-I Heard You Were On A Date, And It Made Me Kind Of Crazy.

34:44.170 --> 34:46.989
Are You Serious? You Got Jealous?

34:47.170 --> 34:48.550
Oh,No,No,No. We Are Not...

34:48.719 --> 34:52.270
We're Friends. He Got Another Girl Pregnant.

34:52.610 --> 34:56.070
Betty. What? I Can Deal With It. I'm Sure Hcan.

34:56.219 --> 34:57.150
Rose For Your Pretty Lady?

34:57.330 --> 34:59.350
Oh,No,She's Not My Pretty Lady.

34:59.530 --> 35:02.360
I Mean,She's Pretty, Uh,But...

35:02.550 --> 35:04.710
He Got Another Girl Pregnant. Oh.

35:08.020 --> 35:08.910
Oh.

35:10.540 --> 35:14.110
You Know What? Suddenly I'm Not So Hungry.

35:14.400 --> 35:15.900
Wait,Betty,Wait.

35:16.060 --> 35:19.020
No,We Can Do This. You Mean So Much To Me.

35:19.190 --> 35:21.470
Oh,My God, He's Proposing!

35:21.640 --> 35:22.510
What? What? No,No.

35:22.700 --> 35:25.880
(Man) Champagne For The Happy Couple. No,No. No,No,I'm Not.

35:26.040 --> 35:29.830
Wait. I Would,But...

35:29.990 --> 35:32.450
I Can't Do This.

35:34.760 --> 35:36.110
No,Uh...

35:43.300 --> 35:44.480
You Okay?

35:44.660 --> 35:46.140
Where Are Ey?

35:46.510 --> 35:47.740
Down In The Kitchen.

35:47.910 --> 35:50.750
She's Licking Fondue Cheese Off His Fingers.

35:51.940 --> 35:53.230
What's Wrong?

35:54.490 --> 35:56.210
I Remember Everything.

35:56.380 --> 35:57.990
Dad's Been Lying To Me This Whole Time,

35:58.170 --> 36:00.180
Acting Like Some Loving Father.

36:00.340 --> 36:01.210
He Hates Me.

36:01.380 --> 36:03.970
No,He Doesn't. He Just Wanted To Use The Accident

36:04.150 --> 36:06.050
As A Way To Start Over With You.

36:06.220 --> 36:09.960
I Remember The Accident,Too. It Wasn't Your Fault.

36:10.280 --> 36:11.480
What?

36:13.230 --> 36:15.670
We Took Dad's Car, And I Had...

36:15.820 --> 36:17.820
I'd--I'd Paid Someone To,Um...

36:19.210 --> 36:21.320
To Cut The Brakes.

36:21.480 --> 36:23.820
What? No,You Didn't.

36:23.990 --> 36:25.560
Yes,I Did.

36:25.730 --> 36:29.150
He Was Trying To Get Rid Of Me, And So I Was Trying To...

36:29.310 --> 36:31.290
What? Kill Him?

36:31.470 --> 36:33.810
Oh,God. Alexis,What The Hell Is Wrong With You?

36:33.980 --> 36:37.450
I Was Torturing Myself. I Thought <I>I</I> Put You In A Coma.

36:37.620 --> 36:40.110
All This Time You Wanted To Murder Our Father?

36:40.260 --> 36:41.950
Daniel,I'm Sorry.

36:42.120 --> 36:44.760
Please Don't Tell Him.

36:48.320 --> 36:50.410
Wouldn't Believe Me Anyway.

37:00.590 --> 37:03.680
So You Had A Big Day,Huh?

37:03.840 --> 37:06.800
Stealing A Car, Crashing A Car.

37:08.010 --> 37:10.530
I Think We Should Talk About It.

37:14.240 --> 37:15.140
Are You Serious?

37:15.300 --> 37:17.340
Yeah,I Know You Think I Haven't Been Paying Attention

37:17.500 --> 37:19.410
To What's Been Going On Lately,

37:19.580 --> 37:21.830
And Maybe I Haven't, But That's Gonna Change.

37:22.010 --> 37:25.900
Oh,So Now You're Gonna Turn Back Into A Mother?

37:26.250 --> 37:27.750
What's That Supposed To Mean?

37:27.910 --> 37:30.680
It's Not Exactly A Part-Time Job When You Feel Like It.

37:30.840 --> 37:32.290
Oh,No, Get The Hell Back Here.

37:32.470 --> 37:33.880
I <I>Am</I> Your Mother. Don't You Forget It.

37:34.040 --> 37:36.710
Let Go Of Me. No,Justin,Listen.

37:36.870 --> 37:37.840
A Kid Losing His Father--

37:38.010 --> 37:41.440
That Is Not Supposed To Happen.

37:43.360 --> 37:46.240
And I Would Do Anything-- Anything In The World

37:46.400 --> 37:49.080
If I Could Bring Him Back.

37:49.740 --> 37:54.300
But... It's Just You And Me.

37:54.930 --> 37:57.250
We're All We've Got.

37:57.880 --> 37:59.690
And I'm Getting Scared, Justin,

37:59.850 --> 38:04.810
Because I Feel Like We're-- We're Moving Like This.

38:08.810 --> 38:12.850
So I Think It's Time We Pull It Together,Yeah?

38:13.010 --> 38:14.430
I Mean,I Been Acting Like An 80 Year Old,

38:14.590 --> 38:17.250
And You With The... With The Attitude

38:17.410 --> 38:19.610
And The Clothes--

38:19.900 --> 38:21.730
That's Not You.

38:22.590 --> 38:25.230
I Just Wanted Him To Be Proud Of Me.

38:25.500 --> 38:28.230
Oh,Baby,He Was Proud Of You.

38:28.390 --> 38:29.610
He <I>Is.</I>

38:29.770 --> 38:33.420
Just Exactly, Exactly Like You Are.

38:36.430 --> 38:38.070
I Just Miss Him So Much.

38:38.240 --> 38:40.470
Oh,Me,Too.

38:42.390 --> 38:44.460
But It's Gonna Be Okay.

38:45.280 --> 38:47.420
Just Let It Out.

38:48.660 --> 38:51.210
We're Gonna Be Okay.

38:55.640 --> 38:56.670
Oh.

39:02.020 --> 39:04.310
If You Had Told Me When I Woke Up This Morning,

39:04.470 --> 39:07.410
That I Would End Up At Your Apartment,

39:07.570 --> 39:09.990
I Woulnot Have Believed You.

39:11.890 --> 39:13.860
Will You Stop Grinning?

39:14.040 --> 39:15.100
You Picked Me.

39:15.280 --> 39:18.680
I Didn't Pick You. I Just Wanted To See "Psycho."

39:18.830 --> 39:21.690
* You Picked Me Over An Underwear Model *

39:21.840 --> 39:23.020
What Is That?

39:23.440 --> 39:25.650
That--That Is A Dance You're Never Gonna See Again.

39:25.820 --> 39:27.460
Exactly.

39:36.600 --> 39:40.850
So What If I Get Scared?

39:41.630 --> 39:43.460
Well...

39:43.890 --> 39:46.290
Then I'll Be Right Here Next To You.

39:59.220 --> 40:01.070
What? (Henry) I Need To Talk To You.

40:01.230 --> 40:03.870
Why? What Could There Possibly Be Left To Say?

40:04.050 --> 40:06.260
I Just Don't Want Things To End Like This.

40:06.420 --> 40:08.630
So You Had To Follow Me All The Way Home?

40:08.800 --> 40:11.070
No,I Followed You Because I Didn't Want You

40:11.210 --> 40:13.670
Walking Alone At Night.

40:18.400 --> 40:19.890
Henry,Please.

40:20.050 --> 40:21.650
Stop. Stop Being So Nice.

40:21.820 --> 40:23.600
You're Not Making This Any Easier.

40:23.770 --> 40:25.130
Well,What Am I Supposed To Do?

40:25.280 --> 40:26.850
I Don't Know.

40:27.010 --> 40:29.410
Kick A Puppy Or Knock Over A Midget.

40:29.590 --> 40:31.310
I-I Think The More Considerate Term

40:31.480 --> 40:33.390
Is "Little Person"?

40:33.570 --> 40:36.070
No. See? This Is Exactly What I'm Talking About.

40:36.230 --> 40:37.810
Well,I Don't Know What To Do.

40:37.970 --> 40:39.040
We Said We Were Gonna Avoid Each Other

40:39.210 --> 40:40.070
And That Didn't Work.

40:40.220 --> 40:42.060
Being Friends Practically Got Us Married.

40:42.220 --> 40:45.200
So What's Left? Should I Leave "Mode"?

40:50.530 --> 40:52.680
Okay.

40:54.860 --> 40:57.380
I'll--I'll Give My Notice On Monday.

40:58.610 --> 41:00.250
Daniel Can Help You Find Something.

41:00.420 --> 41:01.650
Yeah.

41:07.500 --> 41:09.670
Good-Bye,Henry.

41:12.010 --> 41:13.450
Good-Bye,Betty.

41:26.950 --> 41:28.520
There Is Another Option.

41:28.690 --> 41:30.280
There Is?

41:37.570 --> 41:40.580
(Man) * You Must Remember This

41:40.730 --> 41:43.690
I Know You're Leaving In Five Months,

41:43.960 --> 41:46.330
And I Know Everyone's Gonna Say It's A Big Mistake,

41:46.490 --> 41:50.500
And I Know That I'm Gonna Get My Heart Broken,

41:51.670 --> 41:53.660
But Maybe It's Worth It.

41:54.250 --> 41:56.110
Are You Sure?

